1
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:50,950
We will leave through the side door

2
00:00:50,950 --> 00:00:52,410
to avoid the Royal Guards.

3
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:02,750
Lady Dudeng.

4
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:06,520
Hand over the Bronze Soul Lamp if you know what's good for you,

5
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:08,660
and I might spare your lives.

6
00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:10,410
If you dare to resist,

7
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:14,250
I will leave no one alive in this general's manor today,

8
00:01:14,580 --> 00:01:16,640
leaving absolutely nothing behind.

9
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:32,920
Since you don't know what's good for you,

10
00:01:33,830 --> 00:01:36,120
there is nothing more to say.

11
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:03,790
Break!

12
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:04,790
Break!

13
00:02:13,790 --> 00:02:15,700
Your Majesty, I am incompetent.

14
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:17,829
These people are highly skilled in martial arts

15
00:02:17,829 --> 00:02:19,410
and have the help of the Soul Lamp.

16
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:21,540
Please evacuate first, Your Majesty.

17
00:02:24,829 --> 00:02:29,120
Retreat? Then what is the use of you trash?

18
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,790
The Emperor.

19
00:02:59,410 --> 00:03:01,340
The Emperor killed his own guards.

20
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,910
That imperial seal is absorbing blood.

21
00:03:06,370 --> 00:03:07,950
That's not an ordinary imperial seal.

22
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:09,080
It is an evil object.

23
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,870
What a madman.

24
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:18,450
These shadow guards have risked their lives for you for years.

25
00:03:18,450 --> 00:03:19,790
How could you do this?

26
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,579
Hahaha, so what?

27
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,350
They are just a bunch of slaves.

28
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:27,329
How can they compare to my grand plan for immortality?

29
00:03:27,329 --> 00:03:28,950
As long as I have the Soul Lamp,

30
00:03:28,950 --> 00:03:31,500
my eternal empire is just around the corner.

31
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:35,160
Did you think I would care about a few worthless lives?

32
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,750
Now, it's your turn.

33
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,000
Go.

34
00:03:59,450 --> 00:04:01,620
You can run, but you can't hide.

35
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:05,370
I want to see how long you can hide.

36
00:04:39,540 --> 00:04:41,120
General, get on the horse quickly.

37
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:43,250
We have found out that the West Gate is poorly guarded.

38
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,620
We can rush out of the capital from there.

39
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:46,280
It will be too late if we delay.

40
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,000
Get on the horse, let's go together.

41
00:04:56,700 --> 00:04:57,500
You go.

42
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,250
I'll stay.

43
00:04:59,580 --> 00:05:01,580
Ying, come with us.

44
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:04,610
You can't hold off so many Royal Guards alone.

45
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:06,540
Cut the crap.

46
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:08,040
I'm not helping you.

47
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:11,330
I just don't want you to die by the hands of the Royal Guards,

48
00:05:11,330 --> 00:05:13,790
leaving no one to pay back the debt you owe me.

49
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,910
I'll hold off these pursuers.

50
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,000
Take the chance to rush out of the city.

51
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,080
Don't waste time.

52
00:05:44,290 --> 00:05:44,950
Deng.

53
00:05:44,950 --> 00:05:47,370
Let's go. We can't let Ying down.

54
00:05:47,450 --> 00:05:48,580
When we are safe,

55
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:50,909
we'll figure out a way to come back for her.

56
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:55,909
If we don't catch these people,

57
00:05:55,909 --> 00:05:57,750
we'll all lose our heads today.

58
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,409
But whoever catches them

59
00:05:59,409 --> 00:06:00,830
will be heavily rewarded.

60
00:06:00,830 --> 00:06:02,620
My Lord, I have an idea.

61
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:03,580
Although we can't get across,

62
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:04,910
we can throw torches over.

63
00:06:04,910 --> 00:06:06,000
Could she possibly not be afraid of fire?

64
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,660
But the civilians on the street...

65
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:08,620
No buts.

66
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:09,290
Just do it.

67
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:27,580
Damn it.

68
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,060
If this continues,

69
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:31,080
this street will soon be set on fire.
